{"ERS":[{"def":"The bitter vetch (Ervum Ervilia).","pos":""}],"ERSE":[{"def":"A name sometimes given to that dialect of the Celtic which is spoken in the Highlands of Scotland; -- called, by the Highlanders, Gaelic.","pos":""}],"ERST":[{"def":"Previously; before; formerly; heretofore.","pos":""}],"ERSTWHILE":[{"def":"Till then or now; heretofore; formerly.","pos":""},{"def":"The act of becoming red; redness of the skin or surface of anything; a blushing.","pos":""}]}